  <div class="message-body">
    <h4 class="title is-4">Guide</h4>

    <h6 class="title is-6">Name</h6>
    <p class="subtitle is-6 is-spaced">Name of the repository referenced throughout the application.</p>

    <h6 class="title is-6">Directory</h6>
    <p class="subtitle is-6 is-spaced">Absolute path of git directory on the application server. This does not support a remote url.</p>

    <h6 class="title is-6">Branch</h6>
    <p class="subtitle is-6 is-spaced">The prefix of the branch name to run against. For example: <i>/release/</i> would match anything beginning with <i>/release/*</i>. This is run via grep so it supports a standard regex. End the branch name with a "$" to do an exact match only.</p>

    <h6 class="title is-6">Frequency</h6>
    <p class="subtitle is-6 is-spaced">How often you want the scheduler to run a code delta/difference on your repository and branch.</p>

    <h6 class="title is-6">Time</h6>
    <p class="subtitle is-6 is-spaced">When the scheduler should run. This option isn't available for the hourly frequency.</p>

    <h6 class="title is-6">Custom Filters</h6>
    <p class="subtitle is-6 is-spaced">These files, folders, or extensions will also be ignored. Separate via newlines. (e.g. <i>spec/**</i> will ignore any code delta/difference in the spec folder). This support <a href="https://git-scm.com/docs/gitglossary#gitglossary-aiddefpathspecapathspec" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">git pathspecs</a>.</p>

    <h6 class="title is-6">Email Notifications</h6>
    <p class="subtitle is-6 is-spaced">Emails in this field will receive an email notification when a new review is ready to be completed. (comma separated)</p>
  </div>
